The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to create models for predicting health states over time. This falls under the intersection of computer science and healthcare, making cs.HC a likely category. The paper specifically uses Genetic Programming (GP) to generate parameterized dynamical systems models, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The evaluation of the approach also involves comparing it to a generic Long Term Short Term Memory (LSTM) model, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses the fitness function used in the GP framework, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
